### Overview of the problem

This is about the Bulma **CSS framework**
I'm using Bulma **version 0.8.0**
Related issue: #1258 (long text in button outside of the screen)

### Description

At the moment we cannot have long button labels on narrow screens.

![button](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10068060/73524791-2b01f180-440e-11ea-9925-a58c1c0868bf.png)

With a slight modification to the .button class this would be possible:

    .button {
      height: auto;
      min-height: $control-height;
      white-space: normal;
    }

Would there be a reason not to do this? (Like for example compatibility with other form elements?)

